HEADWORD: Notionally
<hw>No"tion*al*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In mental
apprehension; in conception; not in reality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two faculties . . . <qex>notionally</qex> or really distinct.</q>
<rj><qau>Norris.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Notionate</ent>⟦br⟧
